@startuml
title Resource Pooling Architecture - Sibling and Nested Pools

!include ../../../../../../tooling/styles/plantuml/structural/package-diagram-style.iuml

package "Cloud Consumer Allocation" as CCA {

  package "Pool A (parent)" as PA {

    package "Sibling Pools" as Sibs {
      rectangle "Pool B" as PB
      rectangle "Pool C" as PC
    }

    package "Nested Pools" as Nest {
      rectangle "Pool A.1\n(same IT resources,\ndifferent quantities)" as PA1
      rectangle "Pool A.2\n(same IT resources,\ndifferent quantities)" as PA2
    }
  }
}

PA --> PB : drawn from
PA --> PC : drawn from
PA --> PA1 : nested division
PA --> PA2 : nested division

note right of Sibs
  Sibling pools are usually drawn from
  physically grouped IT resources and are
  isolated from one another. Each cloud
  consumer accesses only its own pool.
end note

note right of Nest
  Nested pools are typically used to
  rapidly instantiate cloud services with
  the same IT resources and configuration,
  often per department or group.
end note

@enduml
